title: Mindanao Red-tailed Ratsnake(Coelognathus erythrurus erythrurus)
description: Head distinct from the neck; elongated snout squarish; large round eyes; head greenish brown; some individuals with asblack line passing from nostrils to upper jaw; throat light green.

title: Common Wolf Snake(Lycodon capucinus)
description: amed after their enlarged front teeth, which gives them a muzzled appearance similar to canines, it also makes the snout somewhat more squarish than other snakes.

title: variable reed snake(Calamaria lumbricoidea)
description: commonly known as variable reed snake, is a species of dwarf snake in the family Colubridae . It is found in Thailand, W. Malaysia, Singapore, Indonesia and Philippines.

title: Müller's rat snake(Stegonotus muelleri)
description: the Philippine ground snake, Müller's rat snake, or Muller's wolf snake, is a species of snake of the family Colubridae.[2]

title: Samar cobra (Naja samarensis)
description: also called Peters' cobra, southern Philippine cobra or Visayan cobra, is a highly venomous species of spitting cobra native to the Visayas and Mindanao island groups of the Philippines.

title: Dog-toothed cat snake(Boiga cynodon)
description: is a nocturnal species of rear-fanged colubrid snake endemic to Asia.

title: Vine Snake(Ahaetulla Nasuta)
description: any of several venomous, rear-fanged snakes of the family Colubridae that have slender bodies, narrow heads, and pointed snouts.

title: White-lined Water Snake (Rhabdophis auriculatus)
description: is a keelback snake in the family Colubridae. The population of Rhabdophis auriculatus is unknown
